weeklyTopNews.title: Canberra lifts Victorian border restrictions, but rules remain for SA travel
weeklyTopNews.summary: The border between Canberra and Victoria will reopen at 12.01am on Monday. However, visitors from South Australia will still be required to submit a COVID declaration.

weeklyTopNews.title: 'Biggest test to date': South Australian premier announces new restrictions to combat coronavirus cluster
weeklyTopNews.summary: South Australia will be introducing a number of new restrictions after a cluster of 17 coronavirus cases was uncovered.

weeklyTopNews.title: Three COVID cases detected in SA community
weeklyTopNews.summary: A worker at a quarantine hotel has tested positive for COVID-19, along with two of their family members.

weeklyTopNews.title: NSW Health reports seventh consecutive day of no locally acquired COVID-19 cases
weeklyTopNews.summary: This is the states longest streak since October 7.
